title: Onshape cloud app
content:
Onshape starts ok and displays all page toolbars and the graphics correctly for around 3 to 7 seconds then it all goes blank for several seconds and then only the toolbars etc return. The graphics for the model disappears along with the camera view which shows where the model is in x y and z and also the camera does not move with the right mouse button pressed. See pics below:

L to R - Proof of model existing although not shown in work area 

          - Additional proof of 2nd model not showing in work area           - Actual screen after the display blanks and reappears

It also happens in all web pages but the data comes back, Onshape is the only cloud based App I am currently trying to use. I did install a Xerox print service recently and that needed a .NET update (3.5), after that these problems started. I have uninstalled and reinstalled Firefox from the Mozilla site which cured the problem at the time but it has since returned.

title: gestione del volume durante la navigazione di Youtube, Spotify ed altri
content:
Buongiorno, utilizzo Firefox dal 2007 ho sempre accettato tutti i cambiamenti che la Mozilla Foundation ha apportato senza battere ciglio, ma la gestione dei volumi audio questo no! Questo è troppo! Durante la navigazione su Youtube mi ritrovo ogni volta a dover regolare il volume audio perchè il signor Firefox lo abbassa in autonomia. Ora la questione è molto semplice: o mi viene fornito il modo di ovviare a questo fastidiosissimo comportamento oppure CAMBIO BROWSER senza nessuna altra spiegazione.

Attendo una cortese e urgente risposta da parte vostra.

Distinti Saluti Giovanni Urelli

title: Refresh Option
content:
This may sound really stupid to some but I get really ticked that the 'refresh' arrow is so far away from the URL. I have to use my trackpad to do this and it's a pain to have to go so far. Every other browser has it right next to the address bar. It may sound lazy but I'm 70, have arthritis and try not to overuse the track pad. Harumph!

As you can see Chrome has it right next to the address bar while Safari's is contained right in it. A simple thing but it can make all the difference. Does it but anyone else?
